5 I
). Superior layer of ventral rim slightly tumid near the median margin of the projections of inferior layer (
fig.
5 I
). Ventral rim uniformly excavated, forming a shallow and large aperture, exposing the lateral portions of segment X (
fig. 5 L
). Carinae continued from the conical projection of inferior layer conspicuous (
fig. 5 L
). Segment X slightly wider at base, with inconspicuous boundary between sclerotized and membranous areas; lateral margins concave; apex bearing short setae (
fig.
5 I
). Parameres with apical angle not acutely curved; head not reaching the margin of ventral opening of pygophore; median lobe of lateral margin of parameres, in dorsal view, placed laterally to segment X and bearing long setae reaching the apex of posterolateral angles of pygophore (
